RUN INSTRUCTIONS
Enter the directory where lap3.py and test.sh are in
Start the server by running ./lab3.py
Then run ./test.sh to test 3 servers and show caching.

QUESTIONS

1. Identify the following in the URL: http://localhost:5000/weather/google.com
•Domain:localhost
•Path:/weather/google.com
•Port:5000
•Protocol:HTTP

2. Identify the following in the URL: https://translate.google.com/
•Domain:translate.google.com
•Subdomain:translate
•TLD:.com
•Path:/
•Protocol:HTTPS
•Port:443

3. What is a Python decorator?
A python decorator is a function that modifies or adds to the behavior of another function without
changing the other functions code. For example it could run code before and after the other function.

4. Is there any problem with your cache implementation? Would your cache
implementation work in production?
My cache implementation would not work in production, because the cache grows forever, does not work
with concurrent requests, and is only stored locally during the current process. 